# Complete Repeats

Re-run the entire benchmark suite multiple times end-to-end.

## Quick Start

Add one line below REPEATS,  to your existing `.conf` file:

```bash
COMPLETE_REPEATS=2
```

Run as usual:

```bash
./benchmark.sh -c benchmark.conf
```

## How It Works

**`REPEATS`** (existing) repeats each individual benchmark before moving to the next:

```
server start -> bench(c=25,in=500,out=50) x3 -> bench(c=25,in=500,out=100) x3 -> ... -> server stop
```

**`COMPLETE_REPEATS`** (new) runs all benchmarks end-to-end, then repeats from the beginning:

```
Iteration 1: server start -> all benchmarks -> server stop -> next model -> ...
Iteration 2: server start -> all benchmarks -> server stop -> next model -> ...
```

Both can be combined. With `REPEATS=2` and `COMPLETE_REPEATS=3`, each individual benchmark runs twice per iteration, and the full suite runs 3 times.

## Output Structure

With `COMPLETE_REPEATS=1` (default), output is unchanged:

```
run_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS/
  Model-Name/bf16_tp1/bench_c25_in500_out50_rep1.log
```

With `COMPLETE_REPEATS=2`, each iteration gets its own subdirectory:

```
run_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS/
  iter_1/Model-Name/bf16_tp1/bench_c25_in500_out50_rep1.log
  iter_2/Model-Name/bf16_tp1/bench_c25_in500_out50_rep1.log
  results_tracker.txt      # shared, tracks all iterations
```

## Resume Support

Resume works across iterations. If interrupted mid-run:

```bash
./benchmark.sh -c benchmark.conf --resume
```

Completed benchmarks from all iterations are skipped automatically.
